1. Overview

Exploration Engine (EE-13) is a structured system for generating, transforming, and selecting ideas using 13 archetypal operators (“Coils”).

Purpose:

* Expand idea space (divergence)
* Stress and transform ideas (perturbation)
* Select viable outputs (convergence)

⸻

2. Core Definition

Exploration = controlled expansion and transformation of possibility space under constraints

EE-13 is:

* systematic (not random)
* repeatable
* testable
* compatible with downstream systems (Signal Supply Chain, POL)

⸻

