4. 13-Coil Operator Set

Each Coil = a transformation function applied to the input idea.

⸻

1. Creator

* Generate new primitives
* Prompt: “What doesn’t exist yet?”

⸻

2. Destroyer

* Remove assumptions
* Prompt: “What if this didn’t exist?”

⸻

3. Trickster

* Absurd recombination
* Prompt: “What’s the ridiculous version?”

⸻

4. Warrior

* Stress-test
* Prompt: “What breaks under pressure?”

⸻

5. Sage

* Extract invariants
* Prompt: “What remains true across contexts?”

⸻

6. Lover

* Human desirability
* Prompt: “Would people actually want this?”

⸻

7. Ruler

* Structure & control
* Prompt: “Can this scale and be governed?”

⸻

8. Explorer

* Boundary expansion
* Prompt: “What’s outside the current map?”

⸻

9. Magician

* Transformation
* Prompt: “What can this evolve into?”

⸻

10. Innocent

* Simplification
* Prompt: “What’s the simplest version?”

⸻

11. Caregiver

* Ethical impact
* Prompt: “Who benefits or is harmed?”

⸻

12. Jester

* Engagement / virality
* Prompt: “Would this spread?”

⸻

13. Shadow (Adversarial)

* Exploitation analysis
* Prompt: “How could this be abused?”

⸻

5. Execution Modes

Mode A — Full Sweep

* Apply all 13 coils
* High exploration depth

Mode B — Targeted Sweep

* Select 3–5 coils based on context
* Faster iteration

Mode C — Adversarial Loop

* Focus on:
    * Warrior
    * Shadow
    * Ruler
* Used for stress-testing

⸻

6. Output Format

Each variant must include:

* Idea Name
* Source Coil
* Description (1–3 sentences)
* Use Case
* Risk / Failure Mode

⸻

7. Scoring System

Each output scored 1–5:

* N (Novelty) – newness
* U (Utility) – usefulness
* S (Survivability) – robustness

Selection Rule

Score = N × U × S
Keep if:
Score ≥ Threshold (default: 27)

