9. Integrations

Upstream

* Exploration Engine = idea generator

Downstream

* Signal Supply Chain → refinement
* Artifact Builder → output (docs, PPTs, apps)

Linked Modules

* ZPC → converts outputs to positive-sum
* Kintsugi → repairs failed variants
* Indigo Hammer → stress testing
* Mirror → ethics filter (≥0.7)
* Spider → maps relationships

⸻

10. Invariants

* Exploration must be reversible
* Outputs must be externalizable
* No idea is valid without translation into artifact
* Ethics gate required before deployment

⸻

11. Failure Modes

* Over-divergence (too many ideas, no selection)
* Under-selection (keeping weak variants)
* Narrative inflation (ideas feel strong but lack utility)
* Lack of externalization (stays conceptual)

⸻

12. Success Criteria

EE-13 is working if:

* produces novel AND usable ideas
* outputs can be turned into artifacts quickly
* ideas survive external testing
* others can run the system without creator

